The Council consists of the following members:
The State Superintendent or the State Superintendent's designee;
The Director of the Maryland Virtual Learning Opportunities Office within the Department;
Two members of the Senate of Maryland appointed by the President of the Senate;
Two members of the House of Delegates of Maryland appointed by the Speaker of the House;
The following members appointed by the Governor:
One local superintendent of schools;
One representative of the Maryland Association of Boards of Education;
One representative of the Maryland Parent Teacher Association;
Two representatives of virtual learning providers;
One representative of the business community;
One parent of a student participating in digital learning opportunities;
One school teacher engaged in digital instruction;
One member of the Baltimore Teachers Union;
One member of the Maryland State Education Association; and
One charter school advocate; and
Six members appointed by the Department that are employees of local schools that have excelled in the ability to incorporate technology into the classroom.
